<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>SVB Registration | R G International</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; }
        .dropdown:hover .dropdown-menu { display: block; }
    </style>
    <script src="/RGI/navbar.js"></script>
</head>
<body class="bg-slate-50 text-slate-800 flex flex-col min-h-screen">

    <main-navbar></main-navbar>

    <section class="bg-blue-800 text-white py-16 px-4 text-center border-b-8 border-blue-600">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">SVB Registration & Assessment</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-blue-200 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Special Valuation Branch compliance for related-party import transactions and MNCs.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 px-4 max-w-5xl mx-auto flex-grow">
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-12 items-center mb-12">
            <div class="md:w-1/2">
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-800 mb-6">What is SVB?</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                    The Special Valuation Branch (SVB) is a distinct unit of Indian Customs. Its purpose is to investigate transactions involving imports between <strong>related parties</strong> (e.g., an Indian subsidiary importing goods from its foreign parent company or holding company).
                </p>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    Customs investigates these transactions to ensure the invoice value hasn't been artificially lowered to evade import duties. If you fall under this category, SVB registration and assessment is strictly mandatory.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="md:w-1/2 bg-blue-50 p-8 rounded-xl border border-blue-100">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-4">Who Needs SVB?</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-3 text-blue-800 text-sm font-medium">
                    <li>✓ Multinational Corporations (MNCs)</li>
                    <li>✓ Indian subsidiaries of foreign companies</li>
                    <li>✓ Joint Ventures sharing directors/officers</li>
                    <li>✓ Importers paying royalties or license fees to suppliers</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md border border-slate-200 p-8 mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-800 mb-6">Our SVB Consultancy Services</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">SVB investigations are document-heavy and complex. R G International ensures your transactions are assessed fairly, preventing Customs from unfairly "loading" (increasing) your import duty.</p>
            
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 flex items-center mb-2"><span class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-blue-100 text-blue-600 flex items-center justify-center mr-2 text-sm">1</span> EDMS Filing & Annexures</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">We assist in drafting and filing Annexure A/B and compiling the voluminous documentation required for the Electronic Data Management System (EDMS).</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 flex items-center mb-2"><span class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-blue-100 text-blue-600 flex items-center justify-center mr-2 text-sm">2</span> Provisional Assessment</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Executing PD (Provisional Duty) Bonds and managing Extra Duty Deposits (EDD) so your imports can clear customs while the investigation is ongoing.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 flex items-center mb-2"><span class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-blue-100 text-blue-600 flex items-center justify-center mr-2 text-sm">3</span> Personal Hearings</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Our experts represent your company before the Deputy/Assistant Commissioner of Customs during formal hearings to justify your pricing methodology.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 flex items-center mb-2"><span class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-blue-100 text-blue-600 flex items-center justify-center mr-2 text-sm">4</span> Final Order & Refunds</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Procuring the final Investigative Report (IR), finalizing assessments, and facilitating the refund of any Extra Duty Deposits paid.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="text-center">
            <a href="/RGI/Contact/contact-us" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-500 text-white font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-md shadow transition">Get SVB Assistance</a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <main-footer></main-footer>
</body>
</html>